    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i look in the mirror and i dont even recognize the person looking back. not because i look different, but because it feels like the person who actually mattered... the one with the dreams and the spark... died a long time ago. i'm just going through the motions now. like a ghost inhabiting a body that doesn't belong to me anymore.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you are carrying a heavy emotional weight, and that feeling of disconnection from your own life can be incredibly isolating. Many people experience moments where they feel like a \"ghost in their own body,\" especially when past dreams or passions feel distant from their current reality. It's important to acknowledge that these feelings are valid, even if they don't make sense right now. If this sense of emptiness becomes overwhelming or persistent, speaking with a mental health professional could provide a supportive space to explore these feelings and find ways to reconnect with what matters to you.",
